Yes, killing yourself, by any means is illegal. It's also a mortal sin, which is probably why it was made into a law in the first place.<br>
In practice, you can't punish a person that has committed suicide unless they make a mistake. And if they do survive their attempts, the government has the right to toss them into to jail. Like their life wasn't bad enough, now they're being punished for trying to end their life.<br>
<br>
The only difference between dying of &quot;Natural Causes&quot; and killing yourself is that one takes a little longer. The cause of death is insignificant.  You shoot yourself in the head, BAM, you're done. Pretty quick, although messy. <br>
Or, you could OD from shooting heroin. The effect is the same. The person is dead.<br>
Or you could jump off a tall building. Again, messy, but over quickly. Or you could take pills. Legal pills will kill you just as quickly as illegal pills.<br>
<br>
My point is, we're all going to die. Personally, I'd like to have a choice of what can or cannot kill me.<br>
<br>
For instance, I don't want some asshole to shoot me dead. That, I like being illegal. However if I want to ingest something that will eventually poison me, that's my decision and nobody should be able to tell me differently.<br>
<br>
I wish people would stop being so overly concerned with others, and actually worry about themselves for a change. Of course, that brings us back to victimless crimes.<br>
<br>
Lets say I decide I don't want to live anymore, so I go to the local hardware store, purchase a gallon of turpentine, and begin mixing the turpentine with gator-ade, which I drink outside the hardware store.<br>
Now, as I'm drinking this turpentine cocktail, people are walking in and out of the hardware store giving me looks. <br>
Ok, here's the kicker: According to popular belief, if I drop dead in front of that hardware store, the hardware store is a victim. All the people that witnessed me drinking my turpentine cocktail are victims. Why? Becuase they saw me. They empathized with me, and because I croaked, they now feel bad. Well, I'm sorry, but hurt feelings don't need fucking laws. Natural events don't need laws.<br>
<br>
What we need are laws against unatural events. Shooting someone without that persons consent should be illegal. However, if two idiots want to get up at dawn and face off in a duel, that should be legal. They're both willingly getting up with the intent to kill the other person. If we're lucky, they'll kill each other! If not, well, no insurance coverage for them!<br>
<br>
Flying a plane into a building should be illegal. Planning on flying a plane into a building should be illegal. Talking about flying a plane into a building, even if you're standing in an airport at the time, should not be illegal. Again, talking about flying a plane into a building is a victimless crime. Sure, somebody might get their feelings hurt, but guess what? Nobody cares! I could give a rats ass about how you feel regarding some stupid comment I make.<br>
<br>
Our civilization is being silly. We treat each other like children, and so, we have laws to govern us like children. Nobody takes the time to actually think for themselves any more. Instead they listen to other people and form their opinions based off that.<br>
