Take oil for example. We're dependant on a substance which comes from people we generally don't like, all because we're too scared to say 'Fuck you, I'm growing my gas!'.<br>
The United States could kick it's Oil addiction in less than 5 years. That's right! With just a small modification to your cars fuel systems, you too can drive on Ethanol! <br>
<br>
- It's cheaper than gasoline<br>
- It's cleaner burning than gasoline<br>
- It's a completely renewable source of fuel (Corn)<br>
<br>
The last figures I looked at said that the state of Nebraska could produce enough ethanol for the entire population of the US to drive per year. But instead of allowing our farmers to do their job, we pay our farmers <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not to grow crops</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
